<DOC><DOCNO> AP880705-0088 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-05-88 1102EDT</FILEID><FIRST>d a PM-BRF--PlaneCrash     07-05 0131</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Plane Crash,0133</SECOND><HEAD>Single-Engine Plane Hits House; Pilot in Critical Condition</HEAD><DATELINE>CLEARWATER, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A single-engine plane slammed into ahouse early today, critically injuring the pilot, but three peoplein the house apparently escaped serious injury, the Pinellas CountySheriff's Office reported.   The plane crashed at about 6:20 a.m. northeast of the ClearwaterExecutive Air Park, said Sgt. William Logan. ``The fire there wasprobably from fuel from the aircraft but it is under control,''Logan said.   Logan described injuries to the occupants of the house as minor.   The pilot was taken to Bayfront Medical Center in St.Petersburg, where he was listed in critical condition sufferingfrom burns, said Beth Marshall, director of the hospital'semergency trauma services. The pilot's identity was not released bythe hospital.</TEXT></DOC>